# Task Schema

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Task",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["id", "title", "assignee", "status", "created_at"],
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^task-[a-f0-9]{8}$",
      "description": "Unique task identifier"
    },
    "title": {
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 200,
      "description": "Task title"
    },
    "description": {
      "type": "string",
      "maxLength": 2000,
      "description": "Optional task description"
    },
    "assignee": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["FORGE", "SENTINEL", "LEDGE", "OPERATOR"],
      "description": "Agent assigned to this task"
    },
    "status": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["pending", "in_progress", "completed", "rejected"],
      "description": "Current task status"
    },
    "created_at": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "ISO 8601 creation timestamp"
    },
    "completed_at": {
      "type": ["string", "null"],
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "ISO 8601 completion timestamp"
    },
    "completed_by": {
      "type": ["string", "null"],
      "enum": [null, "FORGE", "SENTINEL", "LEDGE"],
      "description": "Agent that completed the task"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
```

## Validation Rules

1. `id` must match pattern `task-[a-f0-9]{8}`
2. `title` must be non-empty, max 200 chars
3. `assignee` must be one of: FORGE, SENTINEL, LEDGE
4. `status` transitions: pending → in_progress → completed/rejected
5. `completed_at` must be set when status is completed
6. `completed_by` must match assignee when status is completed
